According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Luggage & Bags Market was valued at USD 13.81 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 14.39 billion in 2026 to USD 18.06 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.0% during the forecast period. The market continues to expand as rising international tourism, increasing disposable incomes, and changing consumer preferences fuel demand for premium, lightweight, and technologically advanced luggage products. Innovations in smart luggage, sustainable materials, and e-commerce distribution channels are further transforming the competitive landscape, enabling manufacturers to deliver enhanced convenience, durability, and personalized travel experiences.
